	* exult.cc: look for data folder in .app bundle as well on Mac OS X (and changed the copyright date)
	
2010-02-25	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bugs:
	  #2958487 HQx3 is only scaled to 2x when set in Exult menu
	  #2813106 ES won'tt save frame powers when they don't previously exist
	* ES: Eliminated a few warnings, including Gtk+ stderr runtime warnings.
	  Added missing handlers and missing export. Fixed a few minimum values of
	  spin buttons.

2010-02-24	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bugs:
	  #2179006 Sleeping on the Floor (BG/SI)
	  #2798862 Unconcious enemies stand up for a second before dieing
	  #2796857 SI(?): Sleeping in beds not working correctly
	* General: Eliminated a few warnings.

2010-02-23	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bugs:
	  #2912644 Black rain
		Rain drops/snow flakes/magic sparkle now use shape 0 from sprites.vga.
		Rain drops are frames 3 to 7 (7 being a "splash" frame of sorts which
		looks very nice), snow flakes are frames 13 to 20 and magic sparkle are
		frames 21 to 27.
	  #2798881 guards in goblin valley
	  #2838851 Notebook gump crashes Exult when text is dragged offscreen
	  #2838850 Notebook text is duplicated to the sides of the gump
	  #2805775 Formation is still forced to yes for testing
	  #2957048 Exult.cfg contains absolute paths on Win32
		Exult won't write path settings now: writing the default value is simply
		wasteful as Exult calculates each such default path *once* each run.
	* Applied patch:
	  #2957036 Fix a sfx and fix blacksmith to show tongs and hammer
	* shapes/glshape.cc: Screenshots were causing crashes with OpenGL; fixed.
	* gamerend.cc, gamewin.cc: Wrong xforms were being used in some cases since 
	  evision 6119; fixed.
	* utils.cc: Remove trailing slashes on all OSes when path is added.

2010-02-22	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bugs:
	  #2819210 newfilegump.cc (4 buttons one pixel too far to the right)
	  #2838846 Text background button sticks out 20 pixels
	* gamemgr/modmgr.cc: Removed some redundant variables. Patch dir now behaves
	  identically to mods dir as far as default paths go.

2010-02-22 Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* win32/exult_studio_installer.iss: set to SVN and setting working folder for Exult Studio start menu item

2010-02-22	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed absolute path issue in Windows.
	* Setting a relative <mods> path did not work as expected; fixed.

2010-02-20	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2844723.

2010-02-20	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* exult.cc, Makefile.*, conf/*, files/*, gamemgr/*, mapedit/*: In Windows,
	  Exult and ES will now use/save configuration files, savegames, gamedat,
	  patches, screenshots and stdout.txt/stderr.txt in LOCAL_APPDATA\Exult.
	  This has the added benefit of no longer requiring ES to be installed to
	  the same path as Exult. Existing configuration files (including Exult.cfg)
	  will be copied from the current path to the new location and ignored from
	  then on; savegames, mod data and everything else will not. This should
	  make Exult play nice with Vista and W7, but I need testers.
	  NOTE: If you want to keep Exult as "portable" in Win32 as it was, you can
	  compile it with -DPORTABLE_EXULT_WIN32 and set all relevant paths directly
	  in Exult.cfg to prevent Exult from looking elsewhere. This is turned off
	  by default in current SVN.
	* palette.cc, imagewin/*, shapes/*, usecode/*: Added back width and height
	  parameters to the OpenGL screen grabbers because of ES in MinGW.

2010-02-17	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* OpenGL fixes: Invisibility draws sprites translucently, outlines are now
	  drawn correctly (poison, damage, etc), screenshots and save screenshots
	  work, crystal balls work.
	* Slight cleanup of earlier commit; failed attempt at OpenGL fade in/out.

2010-02-15	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* shapes/pngio.*: Added function to save 32-bit RGBA png file.
	* mapedit/u7shp.c: Do not prompt for palette if running non-interactively.
	* All else: Added a Gnome thumbnailer for SHP files. It can probably be
	  modified to work on Thunar/Xfce too, but I have no idea about KDE.
	  No comments on Windows, though. It is off by default.

2010-02-08	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* ucc: Some additional escape character sequences have been added, as well
	  as some code to warn about unknown sequences. Also, ucc was not closing
	  files it opened, which in some cases causes problem compiling usecode if
	  there are too many includes (e.g., on Windows).

