	* Palette transitions did not load patch palettes (fixes bug #2816773).
	* Fixed bug #2813103.

2009-07-21	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Changing version string to "svn" instead of "cvs" (bug #2822452).
	* SDL video driver on Mac OS X is set to x11 if Exult Studio support is on.
	* Fixed bug #2816756.
	* Added default avatar_data.txt for new games created with ES.

2009-07-16	Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated Documentation,FAQ and README.MacOSX
	
2009-07-15	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* A few compilation fixes/improvements for Mac OS X (courtesy of Dominus).

2009-07-02	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* mapedit/exult_studio.glade: Fixed a couple mislabeled flags in the NPC
	  editing window.
	* audio/midi_drivers/ALSAMidiDriver.cpp: Fixed invalid conversion.
	* data/Makefile.am: Remove error with 'make install'.

2009-06-26	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* exult.cc: --buildmap can now be used for maps other than map 0 through the
	  "--mapnum <N>" parameter Disallowed --game if the game had been specified
	  otherwise (--bg, --si, --fov, --ss).
	* shapeid.*, docs/u7tech.txt, fnames.h, palettes.cc, win32/*, data/*: There
	  were actually 17, not 11, xform tables used in the original games; Exult
	  now implements the other 6. OpenGL/fallback blends are now specified in
	  a file called "blends.dat" (which is bundled in exult_XX.flx for BG/SI).
	  XForms are now patcheable (as is this new blends file). There is still a
	  fallback hard-coded blend set just in case. A blends.dat file is included
	  for new games.
	* shapes/vgafile.*: Fixed memory leaks.
	* segfile.*, msvc9/*, msvcstuff/*, Makefile.{common,am}: A segfile was a
	  stripped-down version of a flex reader used only once; it has have been
	  removed.
	* All others: Cleanup/proper verification if read file object is valid.

2009-05-20	Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated Documentation, FAQ and ReadME.OSX.
	
2009-05-19	Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated Documentation with mods and patch instructions.
	* docs/xml/html.xsl and php.xsl now support coloured tags for manual exult.cfg settings
	  
2009-05-19	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Implemented feature request #2793602 in a way that (hopefully) won't be
	  the source of any trouble.
	* Fixed bugs #2793317 and #2793229.
	* Several destructors that should be virtual but weren't are now. Fixed many
	  memory leaks, delete/delete[] and delete/free mixups. Removed unneeded
	  checks before deleting objects. Removed several unused variables. Turned
	  a few 'const std:string' parameters into 'const std::string&'. Fixed a
	  buffer overflow.

2009-05-18	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* mapedit/shapelst.cc: Set frame spin upper-bound *before* setting value;
	  this fixes a selection bug in frame display mode. Also, leave page_size of
	  that same spin as zero to prevent another selection bug in frame display.
	* keys.*, keyactions.*, data/si/defaultkeys.txt: Added new call_usecode
	  action, which accepts usecode function name (if available) or number and
	  an event id. This new action is now used for the 'feeding' action ('F') in
	  SI using function 0x615. This function seems to exists only with Silver
	  Seed installed, so the old feeding action has been remapped to 'Ctrl-F'.
	  Also, Implemented feature request #279328.

2009-05-18	Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated Documentation with a lot of changes since Exult 1.2. Work in progress, 
	  not yet finished or proof read, Audio section needs to be looked at by people 
	  who know what they are talking about. Mods not yet explained. Only for SVN, 
	  not for our website.

2009-05-17	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixes to experience value computation.
	* Fixed Skara Brae/New Magincia moongate destinations in Keyring mod.

2009-05-05	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Improved MinGW compilation instructions to cover GTK_BASEPATH environment
	  variable.

2009-05-02	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2785315.

2009-04-30 Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated FAQ a bit

2009-04-30	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Implemented feature request #2784001: ES will now prompt to create a new
	  game if no games are installed or if the specified game is not found.

2009-04-28 Dominik Reichardt <dominus@users.sourceforge.net>
	* Updated Documentation a bit
	
2009-04-26	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2781239.
	* Fixed bug #2781432.
	* Eliminating several GCC 4.3.3 warnings.

2009-04-22	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed more OpenGL bugs; BG and SI intro and endgames play in full now. The
	  Exult menu now works correctly, as do mods and setup menus. Added faster
	  routines to get bounding power of 2 size for OpenGL textures.
	* Fixed a few miscolored pixels in Exult menu logo.
	* Fixed subtitle bug in SI intro -- they would not display if audio was
	  disabled but voice was enabled.
	* Cleaned up BG & SI intro and endgame OpenGL code. Made consistent use of
	  #ifdef HAVE_OPENGL, instead of checking #if HAVE_OPENGL. OpenGL now only
	  clears shapes that have palette rotation when rotating the palette.

2009-04-20	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed several bugs in OpenGL: Cheat menu, shape browser, game menus now
	  work correctly; main (Exult) menu still wonky. BG intro, except for the
	  guardian cutscene, works correctly; SI intro, and BG and SI endgames do
	  not yet work.
	* Fixed mistaken if assignment that prevented changing scalers to anything
	  other than pixel, interlaced, OpenGL and Hq3x scalers.
	* Removed several GCC 4.3.x compilation warnings, including some paranoid
	  ones. Removed several unused variables, and optimized the memory layout
	  of a few classes.

2009-04-18	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Applied variation of patch #2272014.
	* Fixed bug #1598910 and #2764270. The latter was done by tying scalers and 
	  scales more tighly; except for point, interlaced and OpenGL scalers, each
	  scaler uses only its "native" scale, ignoring (and overwriting) the value
	  in exult.cfg.
	* Some lerping code is now executed only if lerping is enabled.
	* Fixed a few bugs in OpenGL code, eliminating several crashes. OpenGL now
	  will correctly set lighting, though this may come at a performance hit.
	  The Exult menu and game menus/intros sort of work now, but the cheat
	  screen and shape browser are still broken. The MinGW makefile now has an
	  option to enable OpenGL, and configure.ac now includes checks for header
	  presence.
	* Slightly changed warning options in configure.ac, and make paranoid
	  warnings work again.
	* Fixed bug #2773133.

2009-04-17	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2770944.
	* Removed a few warnings.

2009-04-12	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed crash in SI endgame (and possibly intro).

2009-04-07	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* content/bgkeyring/*/*: LB's crown grants infravision now.
	* content/*/README: Corrected link to site.
	* All else: Fixe bug #2710720. Also prevent similar flicker that happens
	  with invisibility.
	  While fixing bug #2710720, found out the meaning of 3 intrinsics
	  from the original games:
	    - 0x82 (BG)/0x9C (SI): set_light: marks a light source as being equipped
	      or unequipped. Among other things, this prevents a minor flicker with
	      the helm of light when it was being unequipped. It also means that
	      light sources need to call this intrinsic to display correctly as
	      Exult no longer does the work.
	    - 0x84 (BG)/0x9E (SI): set_time_palette: Resets palette to the correct
	      one based on time of day/weather/lighting.
	    - 0x9F (SI): ambient_light: Toggles (based on flag) an infinite version
	      of the cause_light intrinsic. Has been made available for BG too.
	    Based on the intrinsic distribution, intrinsic 0x83 (BG) or 0x9D (SI)
	    must relate to palettes/lighting, but what does it do?
	  Also updated the intrinsic documentation.
	* Updated ucxt slightly.

2009-04-06	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Prevent exclusive gloves from going to the gloves spot due to paperdoll
	  data.

2009-03-31	Lanica Dragon (Phillip T. George <me@PhillipGeorge.com>)
	* Added the Windows Mobile 6.0 Professional SDK (ARMV4I) platform to
	  MSV9 and tested.

2009-03-29	Lanica Dragon (Phillip T. George <me@PhillipGeorge.com>)
	* Made it so MSVC9 could compile Exult (just tested for Pocket PC 2003
	  (ARMV4) and Windows Mobile 5.0 Pocket PC SDK (ARMV4I) Releases

2009-03-28	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bugs #2717401, #2717420 and possibly many others not reported yet.

2009-03-27	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2694945.
	* Fixed bug #2716264.
	* Fixed incorrect tag written by ES when setting title/codepage.

2009-03-14	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* actors.cc: Fixed bug #2687078.
	* objs/eggs.cc: Check mapeditor flag first.
	* objs/objs.cc, shapes/shapeinf.cc: Moved barge seat rotation code to the
	  overall rotation function.
	* shapeid.h: Implemented simple cache for shape information, wasting memory
	  for performance.
	* files/U7obj.h: Fixing memory leak.
	* shapes/*.h: Fixed memory leaks.
	* Fixed several warnings, including a mistaken assignment in an if and many
	  missing return values in non-void functions.

2009-03-13	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* General: Unified ready types and paperdolls for BG and SI. BG and SI Ready
	  types are converted on load to Exult's (and back when saving), and the
	  only differences between BG and SI ready types/paperdolls being the shape
	  and paperdoll data. Expecting many bugs...
	  Added optional secondary and tertiary ready spots for shapes, to de-hard-
	  code alternate spots and BG cloaks.
	  Added frame powers for shapes, de-hard-coding swamp boots. Such equipment-
	  granted powers, as well as equipment-granted immunities are now cached.
	  Fixed bug #2682606; moreover, shapes of NPCs that cause earthquakes have
	  been de-hard-coded.
	  Types of barge parts, and barge classes, have been de-hard-coded.
	* actors.cc: Fixed bug #2682648. More slots call usecode when initializing
	  from a savegame.
	* drag.cc: Fixed bug #2683129.
	* imagewin/*: Reorganized scaler code, and split them into their own files,
	  by similarity. This should help with the OpenBSD memory issues reported
	  in bug #1681788.
	* objs/jawbone.cc: Removed unnecessary check.
	* schedule.cc: Fixed bug in patrol schedule.
	* shapes/shape_inf.cc: Fixed bug in copy function and unitialized variables
	  in constructors.
	* shapes/shapevga.cc, shapewrite.cc: The classes Functor_data_reader and
	  Functor_data_writer required too much information they didn't use; this
	  information is now required by the functors they use.
	* Fixed bug on monsters and quake-on-walk. Fixed incorrect initial values
	  of ready types. Some Doxygenification.
	* Fixed compilation bug due to missing include.
	* Added unoptimized debug mode with heavy GDB symbols.

2009-03-10	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed recently-introduced bug in npc_nearby intrinsic.

2009-03-02	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* palette.cc: Prevent accessing palettes that failed to load.

2009-03-01	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* actorio.cc: Monsters that can't die are forced to have full hp when
	  the game is loaded.

2009-02-28	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* usecode/*: Unswapped UI_set_oppressor and UI_set_opponent in BG and SI
	  intrinsic tables. Confirmed with some custom usecode and the cheat screen
	  in the original games. Fixed UI_play_music to accept > 356 NPCs.
	  UI_npc_nearby only accepts NPCs, and doesn't report them if they are
	  dead, asleep or paralyzed; UI_npc_nearby2 doesn't seem to be affected by
	  those flags, though. Removed special case for Freedom in UI_move_object,
	  as it no longer seems to be neccessary. In UI_clone, have the cloned
	  NPC be friendly, not the original monster *and* the clone. Added safety
	  clause in UI_set_oppressor preventing the NPC from being his own oppresor;
	  also, the unswap above makes unneccessary for this intrinsic to set a
	  target now. UI_get_timer now returns a random value for uninitialized
	  timers. UI_is_readied and UI_get_readied both use the same spot conversion
	  for BG, and the same spot conversion for SI. Fixed invalid return for
	  UI_get_npc_id when given anything but an NPC.
	* docs/exult_intrinsics.txt: Massive update with format changes.
	* Actors.cc: When an NPC is defeated, others NPCs attacking him will switch
	  to new targets. Also, when setting a new target for a NPC, the NPC's
	  oppressor, if any, is reset if he is not actually attacking the NPC.
	* content/*/*: Unswapped the above intrinsics. Removed UCC compilation
	  warnings about missing 'void' in function declarations.
	* schedule.cc: Increased maximum distance at which party members will sit
	  still if the avatar is not moving (fixes Stefano in Freedom).
	* ready.h, mapedit/*: Moved ready.h to shapes/ready.h, and added several
	  new constants used in usecode. These constants are now used in Exult
	  Studio. Fixed some errors in the shape class conversion in ES.
	* actorio.cc: Monsters that can't die are forced to have at least 1hp when
	  the game is loaded (fixes bug #2641856).
	* Make NPCs more aggressive about fighting back, and added more cases where
	  invisible NPCs join the fight (fixes bug #2641154).
	* Fixed serpent bond bug in SI Fixes.

2009-02-26	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed bug #2638479.
	* Allowing NPCs in sleep schedule to do stuff again.

2009-02-25	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fix for multithreaded build (make -j <n>).
	* Fixed recently introduced compilation issue in GCC 4.0.

2009-02-24	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed recent ES performance hit when toggling frames display.
	* Fixed condition check for shape right-click in ES.
	* Fixed hash_utils.h once and for all, and added proper check in configure.ac.

2009-02-23	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed several bugs from the tracker: #1559936, #1851478, #2121276, #2127362,
	  #2127508, #2122907, #2454975
	* Modified a few constants to be less dependant on the tile size being 8px.
	* Foes struck by magebane will seek a new weapon after being hit if they
	  lost their spells.
	* Prevent stats from being set outside the [0, 60] range by the cheat screen;
	  HPs are the sole exception, being settable in the [-50, 60] range.
	* Added FoV and SS to the list of games that do not change the screen size
	  when started from the commandline.
	* Applied part of patch #2348451, and a modified patch #2371363.
	* Eliminated more GCC 4.3.x compilation warnings.
	* Fixed goblin spawns in Fawn Tower. Contrary to popular opinion, it has
	  nothing at all to do with pikemen in the area or finishing off the goblins
	  in the area: monster eggs in SI simply do not seem to hatch in SI if the
	  egg's Z-coordinate differs by more than 4 units from the avatar's when the
	  egg is cached in. Also, extended jukebox egg behavior to other sound eggs.

2009-02-22	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* UCC: Added optional 'void' keyword to specify an usecode function without
	  returns (and warnings for missing that keyword). Improved handling of UCC
	  structs, and allowed them as function arguments and returns; fixed bug
	  with class member struct variables. Made #include directive include a file
	  only once, like PHP's #include_once.
	  Added 'nested' option to 'converse' blocks to force UCC to push/pop the
	  answers on start/end of the converse block; used as follows:
	  	converse : nested (options) { case-list }
	* Keyring: Added 'void' keyword to eliminate warnings.

2009-02-11	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* objs/contain.cc: Prevent avatar from being dragged into containers.
	* UCC: Function calls can now be class expressions too, and be used in the
	  right hand side of a class assignment.
	* All others: Use filename definitions instead of literals.
	* Keyring: Fixed problem meditating in shrine of spirituality.

2008-11-25	Marzo Sette Torres Junior <marzojr@yahoo.com>
	* Fixed problem with playing Ogg in a non-IFF endgame.dat. Fixed SI intro/
	  endgame using hardcoded paths instead of those passed to constructor.

